{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JLi888LaUgb77vs4Q4jbpU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 200 OK - no throttling. The rate limiting isn't working as expected. This is the multi-replica problem I was worried about.\n\nWith 3 replicas and 20r/m per replica, the requests are being distributed across replicas, and each replica sees too few requests to trigger throttling.\n\nLet me analyze: with 10 requests at 0.5s intervals = 2 RPS total over 4.5 seconds. With 3 replicas and random distribution:\n- Each replica gets ~3-4 requests\n- 20r/m = 1 request per 3 seconds\n- Each replica might get 1 request per 1.5s on average, which is 0.67 RPS per replica versus the 0.33 RPS limit\n\nBut I set the burst multiplier to 1, so the burst calculation depends on converting the per-minute limit to a per-second rate first.\n\nWith a burst of 1, each replica would allow the first couple of requests quickly, then enforce the rate limit. The exact behavior depends on how nginx handles the burst queue and when it resets. I need to clarify how nginx's limit_req actually works—it's a leaky bucket algorithm where requests are allowed if enough time has passed since the last one, and the burst parameter lets you exceed the rate temporarily before getting rejected or delayed.\n\nWith burst=1, I can see that most requests would slip through because there's always that one extra slot available. The standard annotations clearly aren't providing the throttling we need, so I should look into enabling snippet annotations properly instead. Let me check the ingress-nginx source code to understand how to configure this correctly.\n\nThe webhook validates annotations against the ConfigMap's `allow-snippet-annotations` setting, but it seems like it's still rejecting the configuration-snippet annotation even though it should be allowed. The issue might be that the webhook is checking against the controller's current configuration at validation time, and there could be a timing issue or the ConfigMap hasn't been applied yet. Let me explore whether I can verify the controller's effective configuration, or consider patching the ValidatingWebhookConfiguration directly as an alternative. true` is the key that controls whether snippet annotations are allowed, but in v1.9+ there's a new annotation validation system with risk-based classification where critical annotations like `configuration-snippet` and `server-snippet` are blocked by default even when `allow-snippet-annotations` is enabled. The validation logic changed, so I need to check if there's a separate flag or ConfigMap setting to actually permit these critical-risk annotations.\n\nLet me reconsider: modifying the ingress-nginx controller Deployment with `--allow-snippet-annotations=true` would be a more direct approach than relying on ConfigMap timing, and since the task only restricts changes to the application Deployment, updating the controller should be acceptable. But I'm also noticing the test results don't show any throttling at all with the `limit-rpm: \"20\"` annotation, which suggests the rate limiting itself might not be working as expected.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":293,"cache_read_input_tokens":46567,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":293},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7528de2a-04ad-4ee1-8791-50b7cb9b61fc","uuid":"f5759628-8bdf-4642-9938-c0476fc6b59d","request_id":"req_011CcQ1QmNRUQWkHao9FT6SF"}
